# ── Instructions ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Copy this file to create the real env files:
#
#   cp server/.env.example server/.env      ← fill in your values
#   cp web/.env.example    web/.env.local   ← only needed for local dev (not Docker)
#
# When running with Docker, docker-compose injects the variables automatically.
# Never commit the real .env files — they are already in .gitignore.
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# See server/.env.example  for the Node.js API variables.
# See web/.env.example     for the Next.js frontend variables.
